solution: ```class StockSpanner {
    private final Deque<int[]> stack;

    public StockSpanner() {
        stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
    }

    public int next(int price) {
        int span = 1;
        while (!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek()[0] <= price) {
            span += stack.pop()[1];
        }
        stack.push(new int[]{price, span});
        return span;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1) amortized per next call, O(N) worst-case for N calls
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a monotonic stack to store (price, span) pairs. Each price is pushed and popped at most once, giving amortized O(1) per next call. The stack collapses consecutive smaller prices into a single entry, avoiding repeated scans.

